dd.pre:
The automatically generated file 00lib/approved.lst gives all the texts which are considered part of the project. You can choose how that list is made:
(a) "atf" harvests p-numbers and q-numbers from the ATF files in 00atf/ ;
(b) "catalog" takes all the p- and q-numbers from the project's catalogue (if it has one);
(c) "mixed" finds all the p- and q-numbers that are in the ATF files and/or the catalogue (but you will have to make deletions manually);
(d) "static" makes no changes to 00lib/approved.lst (which you will have to edit by hand if you want to change it);
(e) "umbrella" generates 00lib/approved.lst from all the approved.lst's in the project's subprojects.
